text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!PhonologicalPhenomenaInSpokenLanguages]]%0a%0a!Nasal Assimilation in Japanese%0a%0a:Author: JacobF%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aThe nasal assimilation of the syllable ん in Japanese%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIn Japanese (Japonic), every syllable follows CV patterning except for the lone syllable represented by the hiragana ん. This syllable is typically pronounced /n/, but it undergoes extensive assimilation within the language, based on the sound immediately following it. %0a%0aBefore dentals and alveolars (/n/, /t/, /d/, or /s/), ん is realized as /n/,%0aEx: せんせい%3csensee> is pronounced [senseː]%0a%0aWhen it is followed by a bilabial sound (/m/, /p/, or /b/), ん is realized as /m/,%0aEx: せんぱい%3csenpai> is pronounced [sempai]%0a%0aWhen it is followed by a velar sound (/k/ or /g/), ん is realized as the velar nasal /ŋ/,%0aEx: まんが%3cmanga> is pronounced [maŋga]%0a%0aFinally, before vowels or word-finally, ん is unpronounced (or, sometimes, realized as the uvular nasal ɴ), and the preceding vowel is nasalized,%0aEx: にほん%3cnihon> is pronounced [nihõ]%0a%0aIn nasal assimilation, the mouth moves early to the position it will be in for the next sound, and the nasal sound is pronounced there, alongside that following sound. In the case of a vowel coming after, or word-finally, the mouth is open and the tongue/lips aren't making contact, leading the /n/ to either disappear or become uvular, and in both cases nasalizing the previous vowel as a result.%0a%0aSources:%0aVance, Timothy J. (2008), The Sounds of Japanese, Cambridge University Press, ISBN 978-0-5216-1754-3%0aAn Integrated Course in Elementary Japanese, by Eri Banno et al., The Japan Times, 2011, p. 27. %0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: A:)%0a(:Category: PhonologicalPhenomenaInSpokenLanguages:)
